			"fontSize": 16,
			"fontFamily": 3,
			"text": "* Gas particles inside a container can be considered as \n  a point mass (as volume of gas <<< volume of container)\n\n* Each gas particle is considered as an independent \n  particle (as inter-molecular bonds are weak)\n\n* Total elastic collisions are taken place among gas \n  particles and the container wall (as particles\n  move with random motion)\n\n* Time taken for a collision is negligible (compared\n  with the time for 2 consecutive collisions is much\n  greater)",
